subsection.p:
Now write a general linear change of variables as

  \begin{pmatrix}
  x\\y
  \end{pmatrix}
  =
  A
  \begin{pmatrix}
  u\\v
  \end{pmatrix}
  +
  \mathbf p_0,

where

  A=
  \begin{pmatrix}
      a \amp b\\
      c \amp d
  \end{pmatrix}

and \mathbf p_0 is a fixed translation.

In form language, this sign is automatic. If x=au+bv, \qquad y=cu+dv, then dx=a\,du+b\,dv, and dy=c\,du+d\,dv. Therefore
dx\wedge dy \amp= (a\,du+b\,dv)\wedge(c\,du+d\,dv) \amp= (ad-bc)\,du\wedge dv \amp= (\det A)\,du\wedge dv.
So \boxed{dx\wedge dy=(\det A)\,du\wedge dv.}
